1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:46,000
=Episode 23=

16
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,640
Rao Yuci.

17
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:49,159
Aren't you quite the strategist?

18
00:01:50,239 --> 00:01:51,560
But in today's "strategy",

19
00:01:51,599 --> 00:01:53,719
the three of us have just witnessed

20
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:55,280
your emotional instability

21
00:01:55,439 --> 00:01:56,760
and your psychotic episode.

22
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:49,500
(Happy Birthday)

23
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:10,240
Yuci!

24
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,319
Yuci!

25
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:13,759
What happened?

26
00:03:15,199 --> 00:03:17,840
Who did this to you?

27
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,159
Yuci!

28
00:03:20,039 --> 00:03:21,919
I'm calling the police.

29
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,639
The police...

30
00:03:22,639 --> 00:03:24,840
Ma'am, please don't call the police.

31
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:26,479
No.

32
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,919
But why?

33
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:31,199
Ma'am, I'm begging you.

34
00:03:33,719 --> 00:03:35,280
Don't ask me why.

35
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,120
Just don't call the police.

36
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,439
Please.

37
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,080
Ma'am...

38
00:03:45,439 --> 00:03:46,879
From now on,

39
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,879
if you want to help me,

40
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,960
don't say a word.

41
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:54,400
Understand?

42
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,520
Hello, Chen Mo.

43
00:04:04,780 --> 00:04:06,540
(Emergency)

44
00:04:08,639 --> 00:04:09,800
It's a deep wound.

45
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,039
How did this happen?

46
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,879
You must be careful.

47
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:14,759
Don't let any water touch the wound.

48
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:17,639
It would be a shame
to have a scar on your lovely face.

49
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:19,720
Remember to take your antibiotics.

50
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,560
How did it happen?

51
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:35,720
Who did this?

52
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:38,040
Was it Bai Liangliang?

53
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,360
Was it her?

54
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,120
Say something!

55
00:04:46,439 --> 00:04:47,800
Chen Mo, calm down.

56
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:50,040
I just had a fall.

57
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,600
It has nothing to do with anyone else.

58
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:54,759
A fall?

59
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:57,079
You fell and ended up covered in blood?

60
00:04:59,319 --> 00:05:00,800
I told you, I fell.

61
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:05,199
Come with me to see someone.

62
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,120
I need to see Rao Shusheng.

63
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:35,920
Yuci.

64
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:37,959
What happened to your face?

65
00:05:40,759 --> 00:05:41,759
You're awake.

66
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:45,000
Then tell me,

67
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,879
what Bai Liangliang telling is the truth?

68
00:05:54,079 --> 00:05:55,480
You recognize this, don't you?

69
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,480
I want to hear it from you.

70
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:03,279
What exactly is going on?

71
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:05,079
Yuci.

72
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,079
Yunian.

73
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:14,600
You're Yunian, aren't you?

74
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,360
Shusheng!

75
00:06:16,199 --> 00:06:17,000
Yunian.

76
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,399
You have to be careful
of the other child.

77
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,759
She's going to be the death of you.

78
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:25,360
Don't let her hear this.

79
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,759
She mustn't hear this.

80
00:06:31,090 --> 00:06:31,920
Don't let her hear...

81
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,900
- Shusheng!
- Mrs. Rao!

82
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,000
Mrs. Rao!

83
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,800
- She mustn't hear us!
- Take him back inside.

84
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,720
Don't let her hear us!

85
00:06:37,199 --> 00:06:38,000
She mustn't hear us!

86
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,959
I'm Yuci!

87
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,720
Yuci.

88
00:06:41,879 --> 00:06:43,120
Yuci.

89
00:06:44,639 --> 00:06:45,639
He's just sick.

90
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:46,800
He's sick.

91
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:48,319
He's unwell.

92
00:06:48,319 --> 00:06:49,560
He's talking nonsense.

93
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,000
Even when he wasn't sick,

94
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,519
wasn't he always like this?

95
00:06:56,959 --> 00:06:57,959
When he was well,

96
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,399
didn't he hate me just the same?

97
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,800
Didn't he fear me?

98
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:03,600
Didn't he loathe me?

99
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:07,759
I hate him too.

100
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,920
Every time he screamed at me,

101
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,920
even though I never understood why,

102
00:07:17,199 --> 00:07:18,800
I still felt like

103
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,240
it was okay.

104
00:07:22,759 --> 00:07:24,199
I thought I had time.

105
00:07:24,199 --> 00:07:25,439
A chance to make peace with him.

106
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,040
After all, I am his daughter.

107
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:33,759
I thought I could
make him see me differently.

108
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:38,439
But today...

109
00:07:41,079 --> 00:07:42,319
Chen Mo, I've suddenly realized

110
00:07:42,319 --> 00:07:43,839
there are so many things

111
00:07:45,759 --> 00:07:46,639
I never knew.

112
00:07:55,959 --> 00:07:57,399
He hid

113
00:07:59,319 --> 00:08:01,519
so many things from me.

114
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,120
All he remembers...

115
00:08:04,519 --> 00:08:07,120
All he remembers is
that "monster" side of me.

116
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:09,079
All he remembers is that

117
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:11,120
I killed his other child.

118
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,560
But what did I do wrong?

119
00:08:13,879 --> 00:08:15,879
What did I do wrong?

120
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,360
Yuci.

121
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,600
I know the truth.

122
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:27,240
But that truth

123
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,519
will only cause you more pain.

124
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:36,840
What do you mean?

125
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,360
You've known all along, haven't you?

126
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:48,559
Everyone knew.

127
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:53,240
I'm the only one who didn't.

128
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,039
Is that it?

129
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,200
The truth

130
00:08:58,519 --> 00:08:59,879
would hurt you.

131
00:09:00,279 --> 00:09:02,159
You shouldn't have taken away

132
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:04,399
my right to know the truth.

133
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:08,000
Especially when I'm consumed by hate.

134
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,759
I'm so full of confusion.

135
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,080
Isn't this all because

136
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,399
of Rao Shusheng?

137
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,279
Yuci.

138
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,519
You've done nothing wrong.

139
00:09:17,279 --> 00:09:18,600
Listen to me.

140
00:09:18,879 --> 00:09:19,960
I don't want to believe

141
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,360
any of you anymore.

142
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,000
You've all been lying to me.

143
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:29,120
Hear me out.

144
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,559
I don't need you.

145
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,360
And I don't need you either.

146
00:09:35,279 --> 00:09:36,559
I don't need any of you.

147
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,799
Yuci!

148
00:09:45,679 --> 00:09:47,559
Please listen to me!

149
00:10:25,919 --> 00:10:28,559
Ever since you were born,
we've dealt with so much misfortune.

150
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:29,919
You're nothing but a burden!

151
00:10:29,919 --> 00:10:32,159
Just stay here and leave us alone, okay?

152
00:10:36,399 --> 00:10:37,600
(You're a nuisance.)

153
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,120
(A huge nuisance.)

154
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,000
(Am I really a burden?)

155
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,919
(Am I just a nuisance?)

156
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,360
(Am I really a burden?)

157
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,720
(Am I just a nuisance?)

158
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,360
(They say)

159
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:37,279
(that people grow up in three stages.)

160
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,240
(The first time)

161
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,720
(is when you realize the world
isn't quite as beautiful)

162
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:44,759
(as you imagined.)

163
00:11:45,039 --> 00:11:46,000
To ourselves!

164
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,080
Come on, cheers!

165
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:47,840
Cheers!

166
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:59,480
♪Happy birthday to you♪

167
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:05,559
♪Happy birthday to you♪

168
00:12:09,279 --> 00:12:12,000
♪Happy birthday♪

169
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,120
(The second time)

170
00:12:15,399 --> 00:12:17,000
(is when you're surrounded by malice)

171
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:20,000
(and find yourself powerless.)

172
00:12:24,639 --> 00:12:27,440
You're just a worm that crawled out
of the treatment center!

173
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,080
You're a lunatic!

174
00:12:36,559 --> 00:12:37,679
(And the third time)

175
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:41,320
(is when you see the world
for what it is)

176
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,799
(and decide to fight back.)

177
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,480
(Even if it breaks you.)

178
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:55,980
♪And I'm standing
on the traumatized ruins unbent♪

179
00:12:55,980 --> 00:13:00,060
♪Til the day my kingdom's reclaimed♪

180
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:06,900
(Three Years Ago)

181
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:16,000
Breathe in...

182
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:23,000
And out.

183
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,440
Just relax.

184
00:13:28,519 --> 00:13:29,559
Don't be afraid.

185
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,360
Take deep breaths.

186
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:38,240
Empty your mind.

187
00:13:44,159 --> 00:13:45,000
Is it over?

188
00:13:46,639 --> 00:13:47,960
Is this ever going to end?

189
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,120
Focus on your mindset.

190
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,120
This meditation is a joke.

191
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,039
It's a mess. We're all lunatics here.

192
00:13:56,039 --> 00:13:57,679
A waste of time and a waste of energy.

193
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:01,600
Ignore the distractions.

194
00:14:02,559 --> 00:14:03,759
Close your eyes.

195
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,399
Meditate.

196
00:14:14,930 --> 00:14:15,840
This belongs to Master.

197
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,039
It's a Da Vinci cryptex.

198
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,440
To open it,

199
00:14:18,519 --> 00:14:20,360
you have to crack a five-digit code.

200
00:14:20,559 --> 00:14:21,759
He established a fund

201
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:25,320
named after this very cryptex.

202
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,120
Yuci.

203
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,279
You were right.

204
00:14:33,399 --> 00:14:34,759
In the stock market,

205
00:14:35,639 --> 00:14:36,960
Li Qiang used five-times leverage.

206
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,200
He wanted to win big
to cover the massive hole

207
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,300
left by his gambling debts.

208
00:14:40,879 --> 00:14:41,679
As a result...

209
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:52,879
I should be discharged.

210
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,519
Now is the perfect time.

211
00:15:02,279 --> 00:15:03,080
Please, sit.

212
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:04,679
Director Han.

213
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:07,679
I'm here for my final
psychological evaluation.

214
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:25,919
Still awake this late?

215
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,360
Actually, there's a question

216
00:15:28,519 --> 00:15:29,440
I've wanted to ask you.

217
00:15:29,879 --> 00:15:30,679
Ask away.

218
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:33,799
Why are you living here?

219
00:15:39,519 --> 00:15:40,559
(The year 2014.)

220
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,200
(Bull Market. Prices Soaring.)

221
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,039
- Higher!
- Higher!

222
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,960
(The index hits an all-time high.)

223
00:15:47,039 --> 00:15:48,159
- Higher!
- Higher!

224
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,440
(Everyone thought it was easy money.)

225
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,000
(They all rushed in headfirst.)

226
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,639
(But a few months later,)

227
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,240
(the market hit rock bottom.)

228
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:02,519
In that gamble,

229
00:16:03,279 --> 00:16:04,240
I was the winner.

230
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,240
I didn't lose.

231
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,320
But I never imagined

232
00:16:08,799 --> 00:16:10,240
that in the game of life,

233
00:16:10,799 --> 00:16:12,399
my loss would be devastating.

234
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,320
The Master is truly incredible.

235
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,120
There's always money
to be made with you.

236
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,950
As long as you're fast enough
and ruthless enough

237
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:19,799
to dump your stock

238
00:16:19,799 --> 00:16:21,200
on those suckers early,

239
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:23,240
then anything is possible.

240
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:24,600
Master.

241
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:28,440
I wonder how many people
will be jumping off buildings.

242
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,000
That's their own choice.

243
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,879
We shouldn't interfere, right?

244
00:16:31,879 --> 00:16:32,679
Come on, cheers!

245
00:16:32,679 --> 00:16:33,600
Cheers! Cheers!

246
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:37,500
(Nan)

247
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,399
Hello?

248
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,240
Dad.

249
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,360
I miscalculated. I lost.

250
00:16:44,039 --> 00:16:45,360
How could I have miscalculated?

251
00:16:45,399 --> 00:16:46,559
You useless piece of trash!

252
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,120
I'm in the middle of a meeting.

253
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,600
Don't call me again.

254
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,879
Dad, I want to...

255
00:16:51,879 --> 00:16:52,879
Not now!

256
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,039
We'll talk when I get home.

257
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,480
But I can't go back.

258
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,000
What do you mean you can't go back?

259
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:00,960
I'm sorry, Dad.

260
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,519
What are you talking about?

261
00:17:04,279 --> 00:17:05,079
Hello?

262
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:06,880
Hello!

263
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,200
(Life is but a few short decades.)

264
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,279
(When you're in the thick of it,)

265
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,480
(you don't realize how crazy you are.)

266
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,559
(It's insanity)

267
00:17:33,559 --> 00:17:35,039
(that made things become clear.)

268
00:17:37,119 --> 00:17:38,240
(The man I used to be)

269
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:40,400
(believed he was invincible.)

270
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,920
(I stirred up trouble wherever I went,)

271
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,720
(only to reap what I sowed.)

272
00:17:44,279 --> 00:17:46,160
(I lost the person closest to me.)

273
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,240
(In my utter despair,)

274
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:52,200
(I invested in and founded)

275
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,759
(the Xinkang Treatment Center.)

276
00:18:01,359 --> 00:18:02,319
Do you see?

277
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:05,839
From now on,

278
00:18:05,839 --> 00:18:06,759
this is where we'll be.

279
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,799
With my own hands,

280
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:21,039
I caused my own son's death.

281
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:25,480
Over ten years ago,

282
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,000
I never once stopped

283
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,400
to reflect on any of it.

284
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:31,279
I lost the person I cared about most,

285
00:18:32,599 --> 00:18:33,880
and I lost myself as well.

286
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:37,799
My son

287
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:39,359
was about the same age as you.

288
00:18:41,799 --> 00:18:42,759
Just like you,

289
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:45,720
he was once a mathematical genius.

290
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,440
Three years ago, when I saw you

291
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,000
crying out in desperation...

292
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:10,220
(Nan)

293
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:12,279
(It was as if I'd been
transported back to 2014)

294
00:19:12,279 --> 00:19:14,359
(when I got final call from my son.)

295
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,440
Since that moment,

296
00:19:20,279 --> 00:19:21,079
I've always

297
00:19:21,079 --> 00:19:23,160
thought of you as my own daughter.

298
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,519
When are you going to leave this place?

299
00:19:42,839 --> 00:19:44,200
I'm getting old.

300
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:46,160
And my body is failing.

301
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:49,279
By staying here,

302
00:19:49,279 --> 00:19:51,240
the doctors can keep an eye on me.

303
00:19:51,279 --> 00:19:52,279
But you're different.

304
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,559
You're so young.

305
00:19:54,559 --> 00:19:56,319
You'll recover in no time.

306
00:20:02,039 --> 00:20:03,359
Keep it down.

307
00:20:03,359 --> 00:20:04,160
What are you doing?

308
00:20:05,319 --> 00:20:06,119
Wine!

309
00:20:07,079 --> 00:20:08,559
The young lady is leaving.

310
00:20:08,599 --> 00:20:10,440
We have to have a drink to celebrate.

311
00:20:10,599 --> 00:20:11,279
Wait...

312
00:20:11,279 --> 00:20:12,799
You guys can actually get wine in here?

313
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:17,000
To tell you the truth,

314
00:20:17,839 --> 00:20:18,680
we couldn't.

315
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:20,279
But look.

316
00:20:22,119 --> 00:20:23,720
We can use our imagination.

317
00:20:23,839 --> 00:20:25,039
Yes, imagination!

318
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:26,400
Pour it!

319
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,480
Come on, come on!

320
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,200
You know,

321
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:41,640
we can never stop imagining.

322
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,279
Exactly!

323
00:20:43,079 --> 00:20:44,319
But what is imagination?

324
00:20:45,079 --> 00:20:46,880
It is the greatest treasure

325
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:49,000
the world has ever given us.

326
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:53,799
Here.

327
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,279
Cheers!

328
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,119
Cheers!

329
00:20:56,119 --> 00:20:56,839
Bottoms up!

330
00:21:02,519 --> 00:21:03,359
Mmm, so fragrant.

331
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,400
No, it's spicy.

332
00:21:07,039 --> 00:21:08,480
It tastes like nothing to me.

333
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,720
Aren't we drinking the same wine?

334
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,799
How are the three of you

335
00:21:14,799 --> 00:21:16,279
tasting completely different things?

336
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,480
Listen, girl.

337
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,319
You are strong enough.

338
00:21:21,319 --> 00:21:22,160
Steadfast enough.

339
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,240
Brave enough.

340
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,079
We believe your courage

341
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,359
will shake
the foundations of that world.

342
00:21:31,079 --> 00:21:32,599
This world still needs people

343
00:21:32,599 --> 00:21:33,759
to actually do something.

344
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,119
Otherwise, they will end up like us.

345
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:38,519
That's right.

346
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:40,720
Tonight,

347
00:21:42,599 --> 00:21:43,519
under this

348
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,960
vast field of stars,

349
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,079
we give you our blessing.

350
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:48,480
We hope

351
00:21:49,319 --> 00:21:51,079
you return to that world with courage,

352
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,559
and blaze your own trail.

353
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:53,759
You can do it!

354
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:56,680
Yes.

355
00:21:57,039 --> 00:21:59,000
To the girl who knows no fear!

356
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:02,920
Cheers.

357
00:22:05,799 --> 00:22:06,599
Cheers!

358
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:10,880
Bottoms up!

359
00:22:30,359 --> 00:22:31,240
For me?

360
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,160
Kobe Bryant.

361
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:34,759
The Mamba Mentality.

362
00:22:42,759 --> 00:22:43,559
Professor Yang.

363
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,759
Yours is far too old.

364
00:22:49,319 --> 00:22:50,480
Here's a new one.

365
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,839
I remember you telling me

366
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:54,920
that imagination

367
00:22:55,359 --> 00:22:57,759
is the greatest gift
the world has ever given us.

368
00:22:59,759 --> 00:23:00,559
I hope

369
00:23:01,519 --> 00:23:03,359
you use the new binoculars

370
00:23:04,079 --> 00:23:05,200
to explore the world

371
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:05,960
and even

372
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:07,759
the universe.

373
00:23:10,359 --> 00:23:11,680
Thank you, Yuci.

374
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:15,160
Just send me a red envelope!

375
00:23:15,359 --> 00:23:16,799
I prefer something practical.

376
00:23:19,279 --> 00:23:20,759
Your gift is in your room.

377
00:23:20,759 --> 00:23:21,960
- Go look.
- Bring it here.

378
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:22,680
Go get it yourself!

379
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,880
Stop pushing me!

380
00:23:24,039 --> 00:23:25,279
I still have something to say!

381
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:29,759
Out there,

382
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,480
watch out for those lurking in the dark.

383
00:23:33,079 --> 00:23:34,759
There will definitely be obstacles.

384
00:23:35,559 --> 00:23:37,319
If it becomes too much, take a breather.

385
00:23:37,319 --> 00:23:38,200
But don't be afraid.

386
00:23:39,359 --> 00:23:42,440
Learn to be patient, to wait.

387
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,960
Let everything settle, then start over.

388
00:23:55,839 --> 00:23:57,319
Take care. Be careful out there.

389
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,680
We'll have to stay here

390
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:01,920
a while longer.

391
00:24:02,319 --> 00:24:04,039
Maybe one day, when we're better,

392
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,359
we can visit you for a victory drink.

393
00:24:08,319 --> 00:24:09,359
I've cracked

394
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,680
your cryptex.

395
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:15,640
Go back and see for yourself.

396
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,480
I'm off.

397
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:48,519
(Father,)

398
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:51,640
(this is the last time
I will ever call you that.)

399
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:54,400
(When I was a child, you told me)

400
00:24:55,039 --> 00:24:57,720
(that only by standing at the peak
can you see the most beautiful)

401
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,039
(views in this world,)

402
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:01,480
(and find life's greatest joys.)

403
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:03,839
(Back then, I thought)

404
00:25:03,839 --> 00:25:05,519
(you were invincible.)

405
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,480
(That with a wave of your hand,)

406
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,240
(you could grasp)

407
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:10,200
(anything you desired.)

408
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,599
(I always believed)

409
00:25:12,599 --> 00:25:13,640
(that having those things)

410
00:25:14,279 --> 00:25:15,720
(would make us happy.)

411
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,640
(But later, I realized I was wrong.)

412
00:25:20,039 --> 00:25:21,119
(The summit of the world)

413
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:22,519
(is bitingly cold)

414
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,000
(and endlessly lonely.)

415
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,359
(What we perceived)

416
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:27,400
(to be the peak,)

417
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,039
(hides thick layers)

418
00:25:29,039 --> 00:25:30,279
(of clouds and mist.)

419
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:32,720
(There is unpredictable fate,)

420
00:25:33,079 --> 00:25:34,599
(and the unpredictable human heart.)

421
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:38,000
(If I could live my life over again,)

422
00:25:38,599 --> 00:25:39,519
(I would choose)

423
00:25:39,519 --> 00:25:40,680
(ordinary happiness.)

424
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:42,640
(Even with a simple, modest life,)

425
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:44,160
(I only wish for peace of mind.)

426
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,640
(I don't regret being your son.)

427
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,759
(Because no matter what kind
of life you eventually choose,)

428
00:25:50,759 --> 00:25:52,359
(you will always choose to love me.)

429
00:25:57,319 --> 00:25:58,119
It's my fault.

430
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,640
I'm the one to blame.

431
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:03,799
Please, can you forgive me?

432
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:17,420
(Xinkang Treatment Center)

433
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,200
She's the one who helped Duoduo.

434
00:26:34,279 --> 00:26:35,079
Rao Yuci.

435
00:26:36,039 --> 00:26:36,920
You have to be brave

436
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,599
and find the strength to stand up again.

437
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:39,599
You have to!

438
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:45,300
(Xinkang Treatment Center)

439
00:26:51,519 --> 00:26:52,319
Mr. Han.

440
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:54,440
I invited you here today

441
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:56,359
because I wanted to find out...

442
00:27:00,279 --> 00:27:01,119
what exactly happened

443
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:02,400
between my Liangliang

444
00:27:02,559 --> 00:27:04,160
and Rao Yuci.

445
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:18,960
Take a look.

446
00:27:20,359 --> 00:27:21,240
The four of them

447
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:23,039
have been close friends
since university.

448
00:27:23,519 --> 00:27:24,279
After graduation,

449
00:27:24,279 --> 00:27:25,799
they co-founded

450
00:27:25,799 --> 00:27:26,720
a very promising

451
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,079
business investigation firm.

452
00:27:38,279 --> 00:27:38,880
I know

453
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,359
you must have many questions.

454
00:27:41,319 --> 00:27:42,119
This whole story

455
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:44,680
actually dates back three years.

456
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:52,160
(Back then,)

457
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:53,319
(I was just)

458
00:27:53,319 --> 00:27:55,240
(a small-time blogger
with barely any followers.)

459
00:27:56,079 --> 00:27:57,039
(I stumbled upon)

460
00:27:57,039 --> 00:27:58,279
(Rao Yuci's story by chance.)

461
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:01,079
(I wrote a quick article and posted it,)

462
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,319
(never imagining
it'd get so much attention.)

463
00:28:03,319 --> 00:28:04,640
Do you realize your article

464
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:05,319
made your mom

465
00:28:05,319 --> 00:28:06,519
too scared to leave the house?

466
00:28:07,039 --> 00:28:08,799
Our neighbors think there's something

467
00:28:08,839 --> 00:28:09,680
wrong with our family.

468
00:28:10,799 --> 00:28:11,519
Why is it that

469
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:12,799
your own personal problems

470
00:28:12,799 --> 00:28:14,960
have been twisted
into a failure of our parenting?

471
00:28:17,160 --> 00:28:19,160
Getting an exclusive interview with

472
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:20,440
Lysen's CEO, Jiang Dongchao?

473
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,599
Sure, no problem at all.

474
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,799
(It was because of that article)

475
00:28:23,799 --> 00:28:25,359
(that our paths first crossed.)

476
00:28:25,599 --> 00:28:26,599
On this matter,

477
00:28:27,519 --> 00:28:29,039
I can help you.

478
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:33,440
Thank you for getting me

479
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:35,039
that interview with Jiang Dongchao.

480
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:38,599
You got what you wanted, Mr. Han.

481
00:28:39,079 --> 00:28:40,599
Is there anything I can do for you?

482
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:47,200
Help me investigate
the relationship between these two.

483
00:28:51,599 --> 00:28:54,160
(Through that, I found out
about your daughter, Bai Liangliang.)

484
00:28:56,279 --> 00:28:58,039
(I learned about some of their history.)

485
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,680
This is my turf! Who dares come here?

486
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,400
Hello, Madam.

487
00:29:09,279 --> 00:29:10,559
It's a pleasure to meet you.

488
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:15,359
Hello.

489
00:29:19,079 --> 00:29:19,799
(Later on,)

490
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:21,119
(I met you as well.)

491
00:29:25,380 --> 00:29:26,460
(To Han Congfei, from Rao Yuci)

492
00:29:28,039 --> 00:29:29,759
(But I never imagined)

493
00:29:29,759 --> 00:29:31,599
(that the root cause of everything)

494
00:29:32,519 --> 00:29:33,480
(was actually)

495
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,319
(this very article I wrote.)

496
00:29:43,319 --> 00:29:44,119
(Han Congfei.)

497
00:29:45,319 --> 00:29:47,680
(You don't even remember
writing that article yourself,)

498
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:48,160
(do you?)

499
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:50,680
(That piece)

500
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:52,279
(faded from public memory.)

501
00:29:52,759 --> 00:29:55,640
(It only made everyone more certain
that I was just a mental patient.)

502
00:29:56,559 --> 00:29:58,160
(You used your imagination)

503
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,240
(to write an irresponsible story,)

504
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:01,799
(and it cost me everything.)

505
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:06,440
(That article you wrote)

506
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,640
(on a whim)

507
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,480
(became a defining part of)

508
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,359
(my rock bottom.)

509
00:30:11,279 --> 00:30:12,079
(I had written)

510
00:30:12,079 --> 00:30:13,400
(so many articles back then.)

511
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,079
(I didn't even)

512
00:30:15,079 --> 00:30:16,599
(remember that girl's name.)

513
00:30:17,279 --> 00:30:18,880
(It wasn't until I read that letter)

514
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,000
(that I finally realized)

515
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:22,839
(the unintended mistake I'd made,)

516
00:30:23,519 --> 00:30:24,519
(and the damage)

517
00:30:25,039 --> 00:30:26,400
(it inflicted on that girl.)

518
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,400
After Rao Yuci was discharged,

519
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:32,720
she tracked down your daughter,

520
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,359
Bai Liangliang,

521
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:34,599
Bai Muran,

522
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,000
and Li Mingxuan.

523
00:30:37,599 --> 00:30:39,279
To take down Rao Yuci,

524
00:30:39,279 --> 00:30:41,160
Bai Liangliang first used
company partners

525
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:42,400
to suppress her projects.

526
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:43,839
Then, within the company,

527
00:30:43,839 --> 00:30:45,079
she spread word

528
00:30:45,079 --> 00:30:46,240
that Yuci was mentally ill.

529
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:50,039
Finally, she tricked Yuci's father into

530
00:30:50,039 --> 00:30:50,920
buying a huge amount

531
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,079
of Linwei Lane real estate,

532
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:53,559
saddling her parents

533
00:30:53,559 --> 00:30:55,000
with an enormous debt.

534
00:30:55,519 --> 00:30:56,240
Yes.

535
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,559
And that includes

536
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:58,839
you and Mr. Xu's house,

537
00:30:58,839 --> 00:31:00,200
No. 88 Linwei Lane.

538
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:03,720
Are you saying

539
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,279
that Liangliang
orchestrated all of this?

540
00:31:16,519 --> 00:31:18,039
The article I wrote back then

541
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,000
caused Rao Yuci a lot of damage.

542
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:22,720
But she didn't target me in return.

543
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:26,519
After she left
the Xinkang Treatment Center,

544
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:28,680
I actually helped her
with a few things.

545
00:31:51,140 --> 00:31:55,140
(Benefactor: 3288)

546
00:31:58,150 --> 00:32:00,440
The relationship between
Xian Pengyu and Bai Liangliang

547
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,240
is far from simple.

548
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:04,440
Ma'am,

549
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:06,799
please talk to your daughter.

550
00:32:07,799 --> 00:32:09,160
Tell her to stop living her life

551
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,400
with such malice.

552
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,240
We owe Rao Yuci

553
00:32:15,519 --> 00:32:16,839
an apology.

554
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:19,079
That's why I came here

555
00:32:19,079 --> 00:32:20,240
to lay out

556
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,359
everything I found.

557
00:32:21,359 --> 00:32:22,160
It's the only way

558
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,680
to ease my conscience.

559
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:24,480
Please leave.

560
00:33:11,519 --> 00:33:13,930
Take a guess what are the people
from Baiye doing here today?

561
00:33:14,119 --> 00:33:14,720
Doing what?

562
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:15,720
I heard they were coming.

563
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:16,240
No idea why.

564
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:16,880
Morning.

565
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:17,359
They're here today?

566
00:33:17,359 --> 00:33:18,319
This is news to me.

567
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:20,440
Morning, Boss.

568
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:21,440
Morning, Manager Yu.

569
00:33:21,519 --> 00:33:22,400
No work to be done?

570
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:26,599
Is Yuci here yet?

571
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:27,519
Not yet.

572
00:33:28,519 --> 00:33:29,640
But that's not the point.

573
00:33:30,279 --> 00:33:30,920
The point is,

574
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:32,720
the Baiye Group representatives
are arriving.

575
00:33:33,319 --> 00:33:35,599
Any guesses on what we're discussing?

576
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:39,000
Well, the whole office's gossip mill

577
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,079
is relying on you today.

578
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:00,200
You're here.

579
00:34:03,079 --> 00:34:03,880
Let's go.

580
00:34:13,039 --> 00:34:14,280
Come upstairs with me.

581
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:40,920
Long time no see.

582
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,079
After you.

583
00:35:06,719 --> 00:35:08,280
I heard Bai Liangliang is back.

584
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,079
And she's with Bai Qingyu.

585
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:12,159
What's the deal?

586
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:14,199
Has Rao Yuci come back to work yet?

587
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:16,119
I can't reach her.

588
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:17,719
She probably

589
00:35:17,719 --> 00:35:19,079
hasn't heard the news yet.

590
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:21,239
A call.

591
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:23,580
(Mr. Jiang)

592
00:35:26,519 --> 00:35:27,800
Hello, Mr. Jiang. Please, go ahead.

593
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,239
Yes, I understand.

594
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:39,679
He said our tripartite

595
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:41,559
strategic cooperation

596
00:35:41,559 --> 00:35:42,760
is about to begin.

597
00:35:43,559 --> 00:35:45,239
Baiye Group will send a CFO

598
00:35:45,239 --> 00:35:46,840
to monitor our cash flow.

599
00:35:48,559 --> 00:35:49,360
Bai Liangliang...

600
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,039
I feel like

601
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:58,519
there are things

602
00:35:58,519 --> 00:35:59,679
we don't know yet.

603
00:36:07,340 --> 00:36:11,000
=Episode 23=
(The Answer)

604
00:36:11,580 --> 00:36:14,020
(All animals in this production
were treated humanely)

605
00:36:14,020 --> 00:36:20,220
♪Take a breath and swallow
the words you couldn't say♪

606
00:36:20,980 --> 00:36:24,180
♪No need to force your heart anymore♪

607
00:36:24,180 --> 00:36:28,700
♪Searching for the season
we once missed♪

608
00:36:28,700 --> 00:36:36,220
♪Leave this place,
though wounded still stay strong♪

609
00:36:36,220 --> 00:36:40,140
♪You must believe
one day the rain will fall♪

610
00:36:40,140 --> 00:36:44,180
♪And wash away the mud
that stains your soul♪

611
00:36:44,180 --> 00:36:47,700
♪Find your freedom in the wild♪

612
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:51,660
♪Take your stride and move ahead♪

613
00:36:51,660 --> 00:36:55,820
♪I will stay behind
and wait for your eyes♪

614
00:36:55,820 --> 00:37:00,020
♪To rebuild
the same flesh and soul again♪

615
00:37:00,020 --> 00:37:03,820
♪Wander freely through the thorns♪

616
00:37:03,820 --> 00:37:07,900
♪Keep walking through the light♪

617
00:37:07,900 --> 00:37:12,100
♪Fate is absurd, don't stop for anyone♪

618
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:18,420
♪What you dare to lose
will one day be your own♪

619
00:37:35,540 --> 00:37:42,180
♪I'm sorry, I still owe you these words♪

620
00:37:42,180 --> 00:37:46,020
♪An apology that came too late♪

621
00:37:46,020 --> 00:37:50,660
♪Yet it's also the path
that saves my soul♪

622
00:37:50,740 --> 00:37:58,140
♪When the cold wind
passes it takes the past away♪

623
00:37:58,140 --> 00:38:02,220
♪You must believe and stand unwavering♪

624
00:38:02,220 --> 00:38:06,300
♪There will be hands
to pull you from the deep♪

625
00:38:06,300 --> 00:38:10,300
♪Find your freedom in the silence♪

626
00:38:10,300 --> 00:38:14,060
♪Let your wounds be mended♪

627
00:38:14,060 --> 00:38:18,260
♪Gray is not the past
and pain is not a shame♪

628
00:38:18,260 --> 00:38:22,420
♪Sometimes the sunlight
makes the world look crueler♪

629
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:26,140
♪Wander through the echoes of regret♪

630
00:38:26,140 --> 00:38:30,180
♪Be forgiven and be sheltered♪

631
00:38:30,180 --> 00:38:34,220
♪After everything shatters,
hold my hand♪

632
00:38:34,220 --> 00:38:40,420
♪A flower reborn
will finally bloom forever♪
